===Noun===
'''aketon'''
# (''Archaic'') A [[stuffed]] [[jacket]] worn under the [[mail]], or (later) a jacket [[plated]] with mail.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''':  The aketon, [[gambeson]], [[vambasium]], and [[jack]] were military [[vestment]]s, calculated for the [[defence]] of the body, differing little from each other, except in their names, their materials and construction were nearly the same, the authorities quoted in the notes, [[shew]] they were all composed of many folds of linen, stuffed with [[cotton]], [[wool]] or [[hair]], [[quilted]], and commonly covered with [[leather]], made of [[buck]] or [[doe]] skin. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 15.